			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="323">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>It was three o&rsquo;clock in the morning when, unable to sleep, I turned to <em>The Sun</em> to keep me company. I felt as if &ldquo;<a href="/article/4822">The Hour and the Day</a>,&rdquo; by C.J. Gall [August 2013], were written just for me.</p>

<p>I was visiting my adult son, who is about to be married. He is the last of my three boys to marry, and while I celebrate this event with all my heart, I also feel that part of my life is ending. All my sons have now moved fully into their own lives. My visit had some awkward moments as my son and I navigated this new terrain. I&rsquo;m sure that&rsquo;s why I was awake in the middle of the night.</p>

<p>Gall&rsquo;s essay spoke to another aspect of my life as well. I am the primary care&shy;giver for my elderly mother, who is ninety-seven and losing her short-term memory. Her quality of life is greatly diminished. In these few last months I have realized that I am ready to let go of her.</p>

<p>My feelings about my son and my mother aren&rsquo;t easy to bear. Gall&rsquo;s writing transported me and helped me to see that what I am experiencing is just the great wheel of life making another turn.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Marilyn Hagar<br>Mendocino, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
		<div class="cta cta-l1" data-url="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">
			<div class="cta-intro">
				<h5 class="cta-title alt-ff">Thinking about writing us a letter?</h5>
				<p class="cta-text">Give in to the temptation. We love getting mail. <br><span class="xsmall">(Of course, we reserve the right to edit.)</span></p>
			</div>
			<a href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor" class="cta-button b b-4 b-padding-tight small" data-label="Write Us A Letter!">Write Us A Letter!</a>
